OL,4,CThe tyranny of India's residents'
OL,5,Cassociations
OL,6, Major Atul Dev, a retired Indian army
OL,7, veteran, is on the warpath - against
OL,8, his Residents' Welfare Association.
OL,10,FCommonly known as the RWAs, these
OL,11,Fassociations are a unique feature of
OL,12,FIndian urban living. They are
OL,13,Fresponsible for managing the day-to-day
OL,14,Faffairs of specific residential areas
OL,15,Fand generally set guidelines - relating
OL,16,Fto issues like security - for people to
OL,17,Ffollow. Its members are elected by
OL,18,Fthose living in a housing society or a
OL,19,Fneighbourhood.
